=== Lesson 27-1 (Introduction) ===

 {"type":"h3","text":"Germaine's Guide to RC Application Questions"}
 {"type":"h4","text":"What's this question asking?"}
 {"type":"paragraph","text":"Application questions ask you to take a rule, standard, or theory explained in the passage and correctly apply it to a brand new situation..."}
 {"type":"list","items":["Isolate the specific principle or standard from the text.","Understand the conditions required for the principle to apply.","Find the one hypothetical scenario in the answer choices that meets those exact conditions."]}
+{{+**How This Differs From Analogy:** Analogy questions ask you to find a parallel *structure*. Application questions ask you to correctly *use* a rule. In Analogy, you abstract the logic; in Application, you build a checklist from the rule's conditions and test each scenario against it.+}}
 {"type":"hr"}
